03/12/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- US Deputy Secretary of State James Steinberg met on Wednesday (December 2nd) with political leaders from Republika Srpska (RS) and the Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina (FBiH) about proposed constitutional changes. 
RS Prime Minister Milorad Dodik described his conversation with Steinberg as constructive. 
He said the topics covered included visa liberalisation and the Office of the High Representative.
Separately Wednesday, High Representative Valentin Inzko announced that Steinberg has presented leaders of the main political parties a modified package of constitutional changes. 
He urged the politicians to provide feedback. 
(RTRS, Fena, Dnevni Avaz, Srna - 02/12/09)
